ants

Class AntGameMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • ants.AntGameMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AntGameMapCallback, AntGameMapView

    public class AntGameMap
extends java.lang.Object
implements AntGameMapCallback, AntGameMapView
    This class represents the dynamic game map of an ant game. It holds all the game objects and their status at the current round of a game.
    Author:
    Benjamin

      • cells

        private java.util.ArrayList<java.util.ArrayList<java.util.ArrayList<AntGameObject>>> cells
        The array of cells of the map. This is a 3-dimensional array. The first dimension references map rows, the second one map columns and the last one is used to store several game objects in the same cell.

      • applyMask

        public java.util.ArrayList<AntGameObject> applyMask(int col,
                                                    int row,
                                                    AntGameMapMask mask)
        This method finds all the objects that are presents in the mask. The center of the mask is given by the column and row identifiers. The method takes the toroidal shape of the map in account.
        Parameters:
        col - the column identifier of the position.
        row - the row identifier of the position.
        mask - the mask to apply at this position.
        Returns:
        the list of game objects in the mask.
